-----------------------------------------------------------
BitTorrent for the Peersim Simulator

https://opensvn.csie.org/bitpeer/

Fabrizio Frioli, Michele Pedrolli
{fabrizio.frioli, michele.pedrolli} <AT> studenti.unitn.it
-----------------------------------------------------------

BitPeer is a BitTorrent module for Peersim,
a P2P simulation environment.

An example configuration file (config-BitTorrent.cfg)
can be found in the root directory.

A detailed documentation can be found in manual.pdf.
Please refer to the javadoc documentation for more details.

------------------------------------
Download
------------------------------------

The latest version of BitPeer can be downloaded
from the SVN repository hosted by csie.org.

To checkout the last version, invoke:

	svn co https://opensvn.csie.org/bitpeer/

------------------------------------
Makefile
------------------------------------

To compile the sources, invoke:

  make

To compile the API documentation, invoke:

  make doc

To run the code, invoke:

  make run

To run all the previous command in this order, invoke:

  make all